info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Returns an array in which a zonal statistical metrix has been applied to the matrix represeted by the input array.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure : input measure.
- buffer : zone size (0 means 1 pixel, 1 means a square of 9 pixels, etc.)
- operator name : type of operator
                  -- 'oph_max' : compute the maximum value of a zone (default);
                  -- 'oph_min' : compute the minimum value of a zone;
                  -- 'oph_avg' : compute the mean of all elements of a zoene;
                  -- 'oph_sum' : compute the sum of all elements of a zone.
- missingvalue : value to be considered as missing value; by default it is NAN (for 'oph_double' and 'oph_float').
- sampling : flag set in case data have to be sampled on the center of the zone.

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
oph_zonal_stats('OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',measure)
